0it's%20not%20an%20uncommon%20issue%2C%20according%20to%20experts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you're%20reeling%20from%20the%20emotions%20of%20just%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-having-the-same-couples-fight-over-and-over-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efought%20with%20your%20partner%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Do%20you%20sit%20with%20your%20feelings%20about%20the%20conflict%20and%20then%20talk%20things%20out%3F%20Or%20do%20you%20immediately%20text%20or%20call%20a%20friend%20to%20vent%20about%20your%20partner%3F%20If%20you%20answered%20the%20latter%2C%20you%20might%20be%20what%20licensed%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20certified%20relationship%20and%20intimacy%20expert%20Jacqueline%20Sherman%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Brelationship%20dumper.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20a%20relationship%20dumper%20often%20overshares%20about%20their%20relationship%2C%20especially%20issues%20they're%20experiencing.%20This%20can%20cause%20the%20friend%20receiving%20the%20information%20to%20feel%20overburdened%3B%20they%20may%20also%20develop%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-should-i-do-my-friends-hate-my-boyfriend-girlfriend-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enegative%20perception%20of%20the%20partner%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20discussed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20friends%20with%20a%20relationship%20dumper%2C%20experts%20say%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecreate%20boundaries%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20protect%20your%20friendship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fdc4e71-d1de-499d-b523-7747118204e2%5C%22%3EIt%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20set%20boundaries%20with%20a%20'relationship%20dumper%2C'%20but%20it's%20still%20important%20to%20do%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20can%20be%20frustrating%2C%20overwhelming%2C%20or%20even%20just%20annoying%20to%20provide%20emotional%20support%20to%20a%20relationship%20dumper%2C%20it's%20key%20to%20remember%20they're%20still%20your%20friend.%20There's%20a%20way%20to%20communicate%20boundaries%20while%20still%20maintaining%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20a%20good%20method%20for%20creating%20boundaries%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bsandwich%20technique%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20you%20begin%20by%20sharing%20how%20you%20feel%20connected%20to%20your%20friend%2C%20then%20communicate%20your%20boundary%2C%20and%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-posting-layoffs-online-are-lonely-seeking-validation-expert-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evalidate%20their%20experience%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20try%20to%20help%20them%20find%20another%20resource%20besides%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suggests%20beginning%20by%20saying%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20love%20our%20friendship%2C%20and%20I%20love%20that%20we're%20able%20to%20share%20what's%20going%20on%20with%20each%20other's%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20to%20set%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharing-at-work-stop-oversharing-in-office-professional-growth-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eboundary%20around%20oversharing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20might%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BLately%2C%20I've%20noticed%20that%20you've%20been%20sharing%20a%20lot%20about%20your%20partner%2C%20and%20although%20I%20feel%20really%20privileged%20to%20have%20that%20information%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20help%20when%20you're%20in%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20close%20out%20the%20sandwich%20technique%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20leave%20them%20without%20a%20space%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ve