isten%20to%20their%20issues%20all%20the%20time%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20their%20feelings%20aren't%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20think%20that%20friendships%20are%20an%20excellent%20place%20to%20be%20able%20to%20vent%20about%20things%20that%20are%20going%20on%20in%20your%20relationship%2C%20but%20everyone's%20capacity%20to%20be%20able%20to%20support%20looks%20different%20%E2%80%94%20So%20the%20individual%20needs%20to%20be%20able%20to%20have%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-be-self-aware-at-work-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eself-awareness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20know%20and%20recognize%20if%20they're%20being%20triggered%20or%20burned%20out%20from%20what%20their%20friend%20is%20sharing%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20feeling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburn-out-executive-nightmares-drinking-quit-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eburned%20out%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20hearing%20about%20your%20friend's%20venting%2C%20setting%20a%20boundary%20might%20sound%20like%20this%3A%20%26quot%3BWhere%20I%20am%20in%20my%20own%20life%2C%20I'm%20unable%20to%20assist%20more%20than%20I%20already%20have%2C%20so%20I%20would%20really%20appreciate%20it%20if%20our%20friendship%20can%20be%20focused%20on%20topics%20outside%20your%20relationship%20moving%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20still%20feel%20nervous%20about%20having%20this%20conversation%20with%20your%20friend%2C%20that's%20completely%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20courage%20to%20have%20that%20level%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fhow-to-be-vulnerable%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evulnerability%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20able%20to%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20can%20we%20do%20this%20dance%20differently%2C'%26quot%3B%20Hope%20Kelaher%2C%20a%20licensed%20clinical%20social%20worker%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BHere%20to%20Make%20Friends%2C%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20book%20about%20how%20to%20make%20friends%20as%20an%20adult%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Etold%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Kelaher%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20distinguish%20between%20nerves%20and%20an%20actual%20fear%20of%20communicating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-common-friendship-issues-people-share-with-a-friendship-coach-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efriendship%20issues%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20relationships%20have%20ruptures%20and%20repairs%2C%20so%20if%20you're%20that%20afraid%20your%20friend%20cannot%20handle%20potential%20feedback%20and%20that%20it's%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-ruin-a-relationship-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eruin%20the%20relationship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20would%20caution%20people%20to%20think%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20about%20the%20value%20of%20that%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelaher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229351af4b-9c5c-4159-bbdc-f40532c5a160%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20do%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20venting%20to%20the%20same%20friend%20over%20and%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20who%20vent%20about%20their%20relationships%20beyond%20what%20their%20friends%20can%20accommodate%20aren't%20intentionally%20trying%20to%20cross%20boundaries.%20Even%20if%20you%20feel%20you've%20never%20been%20friends%20with%20someone%20who%20relied%20on%20you%20for%20emotional%20support%20amid%20their%20relationship%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20or%20exhibited%20the%20behavior%20yourself%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20still%20a%20pattern%20Sherman%20and%20Kelaher%20have%20both%20seen%20frequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20something%20that%20we've%20all%20e