he%20startup%20he%20ran%2C%20an%20unexpected%20email%20hit%20his%20inbox%20as%20it%20weighed%20an%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEuropean%20private%20equity%20firm%20Hg%20expressed%20interest%20in%20buying%20a%20majority%20stake%20in%20the%20enterprise%20software%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20getting%20an%20email%20that%20says%2C%20'I%20want%20to%20marry%20your%20daughter%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Arnold%2C%20who%20is%20a%20father.%20He%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20somebody%20is%20serious%20enough%20to%20say%20that%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20take%20the%20meeting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20span%20of%20just%20two%20months%2C%20Hg%20put%20a%20ring%20on%20it.%20AuditBoard%20reached%20an%20agreement%20to%20be%20acquired%20in%20a%20deal%20valued%20at%20over%20%243%20billion%20by%20Hg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-startups-get-bought-up-by-private-equity-vc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate%20equity%20is%20hoovering%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20exits%20have%20tumbled%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%20The%20biggest%20startup%20players%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fservicetitan-waiting-until-after-the-election-to-go-public-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20holding%20off%20on%20market%20debuts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Corporates%20are%20unwilling%20or%20unable%20to%20cut%20deals.%20PitchBook%20data%20shows%20the%20transaction%20value%20of%20this%20year's%20IPOs%20and%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%20is%20tracking%20towards%20%2498%20billion%2C%20an%2086%25%20nosedive%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20startups%2C%20private%20equity%20represents%20a%20deep-pocketed%20buyer%20willing%20to%20move%20quickly%2C%20pay%20a%20premium%2C%20and%20potentially%20help%20the%20business%20by%20tapping%20into%20complementary%20companies%20in%20their%20portfolio.%20A%20sale%20also%20gives%20shareholders%20a%20fast%20pass%20to%20liquidity%2C%20unlike%20an%20IPO%20that%20restricts%20insiders%20from%20selling%20their%20shares%20during%20a%20lockup%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAuditBoard%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20startup%20that%20private%20equity%20goes%20gaga%20over.%20The%20company%20helps%20audit%20and%20risk%20teams%20stay%20on%20task%20by%20providing%20software%20that%20simplifies%20reporting%20and%20data%20collection.%20Founded%20in%202014%20by%20Daniel%20Kim%20and%20Jay%20Lee%2C%20AuditBoard%20is%20used%20by%20over%202%2C000%20enterprises%2C%20including%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20Fortune%20500.%20It's%20been%20cash%20flow%20positive%20for%20a%20decade%20and%20was%20generating%20%24200%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%20in%20February%2C%20Fortune%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22729a3c9f-e4cd-43fd-85a2-8d4df06f5414%5C%22%3EA%20long%20courtship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Hg%20director%20Alex%20Johnson%20wrote%20to%20Arnold%20in%20March%2C%20it%20wasn't%20the%20first%20time%20the%20firm%20had%20come%20knocking.%20Johnson%20had%20asked%20Battery%20Ventures%20principal%20Dallin%20Bills%20to%20arrange%20a%20meeting%20with%20Arnold%20in%202022.%20But%20Arnold%20said%20thanks%2C%20but%20no%20thanks.%20The%20company%20was%20on%20a%20growth%20tear%2C%20Arnold%20said%2C%20as%20enterprises%20looked%20to%20beef%20up%20security%20and%20compliance%20measures%20in%20the%20fallout%20of%20a%20pandemic%2C%20a%20global%20supply%20chain%20crisis%2C%20and%20costly%20cyberattacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20heads%20down%20on%20execution%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnold%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20frankly%20we%20didn't%20need%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%20The%20company's%20last%20funding%20round%20was%20a%20Series%20B%20led%20by%20Battery%20Ventures%20in%202018%2C%20though%20it%20had%20allowed%20insiders%20to%20sell%20shares%20to%20new%20investors%2C%20Dragoneer%20and%20Tiger%20Global.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20time%20Hg%20connected%2C%20Arnold%20was%20in%20a%20different%20mindset.%20He%20had%20discussed%20with%20his%20board%20going%20public%20to%20give%20returns%20to%20investors%20and%20life-changing%20money%20to%20employees.%20The%20company%20assembled%20a%20pitch%20deck%20and%20showed%20it%20off%20to%20investors%20at%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20tech%2C%20media%2C%20and%20telecom%20conference%20in%20San%20Francisco%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20founders%20dream%20of%20a%20splashy%20IPO%2C%20but%20Arnold%20said%20being%20a%20public%20company%20boss%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20bucket%20list%20item.%26quot%3B%20As%20an%20executive%20at%20Shutterfly%2C%20before%20it%20went%20private%20in%202019%2C%20he%20saw%20how%20the%20pressures%20of%20quarterly%20earnings%20could%20shift%20focus%20from%20long-term%20value%20to%20short-term%20stock%20market%20gains.%20He%20also%20valued%20AuditBoard's%20nimble%2C%20five-member%20board%20for%20its%20quick%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20into%20his%20first%20meeting%20with%20Hg%20with%20two%20demands%2C%20which%20he%20credits%20to%20board%20director%20Roxanne%20Oulman's%20wise%20counsel.%20If%20Hg%20wanted%20to%20buy%20AuditBoard%2C%20it%20had%20to%20buy%20the%20whole%20company.%20The%20initial%20email%20had%20said%20a%20majority%20stake%20which%20could%20mean%20as%20little%20as%2051%25.%20And%20Hg%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20range%20of%20multiples%20they%20had%20paid%20for%20similar%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20sitting%20across%20the%20table%20from%20Nic%20%5BHumphries%20%E2%80%94%20Hg's%20senior%20partner%20and%20executive%20chairman%5D%2C%20and%20he%20said%20yes%20and%20yes%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnold%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20this%20was%20serious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220027eda8-35c4-419b-9c08-b4010a3271e7%5C%22%3EBidding%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EArnold%20then%20delivered%20the%20pitch%20deck%20that%20he%20had%20shown%20to%20public%20market%20investors%20just%20weeks%20before.%20The%20second%20slide%20highlighted%20the%20company's%20stickiness%20with%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAuditBoard%20has%20a%20gross%20retention%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20much%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%20is%20retained%20from%20existing%20customers%20over%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20of%20more%20than%2095%25.%20This%20made%20growth%20easier%2C%20Arnold%20explained%20because%20customers%20were%20able%20and%20willing%20to%20purchase%20additional%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20grew%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%20by%2040%25%20in%202023%2C%20an%20impressive%20feat%20during%20a%20dramatic%20pullback%20in%20software%20spending%20across%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20after%20its%20first%20meeting%20with%20Hg%2C%20AuditBoard%20hired%20Goldman%20Sachs%20to%20run%20a%20market%20check.%20The%20startup%20met%20with%20between%20five%20to%20nine%2C%20handpicked%20private%20equity%20firms%20and%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20ended%20up%20with%20a%20crazy%20number%20of%20people%20that%20were%20bidding%20something%20with%20a%20three%20in%20front%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Arnold%2C%20meaning%20billions.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20the%20board%20was%20in%20a%20really%20cool%20decision%20dimension.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20considered%20the%20offers%20on%20three%20axes%3A%20price%2C%20timing%2C%20and%20certainty.%20Hg%20won%20out%20in%20each.%20It%20increased%20a%20previous%20verbal%20offer%20by%20%24100%20million.%20Hg%20was%20willing%20to%20sign%20an%20agreement%20within%20a%20day.%20And%20it%20provided%20certainty%20that%20it%20would%20get%20the%20deal%20done%20by%20agreeing%20to%20backstop%20the%20full%20amount%2C%20meaning%20the%20acquisition%20wasn't%20contingent%20on%20Hg's%20ability%20to%20secure%20debt%20financing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20huge%2C%20huge%20and%20gutsy%20move%20on%20his%20part%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnold%20said%20of%20Humphries%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20further%20affirmed%20that%20he%20was%20really%20committed%20to%20making%20this%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e19a818f-3cc5-4c18-8dab-d7c3535b5e0a%5C%22%3EHappily%20ever%20after%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EArnold%20was%20in%20Paris%20on%20a%20sales%20call%20when%20he%20signed%20the%20agreement%20to%20be%20acquired.%20The%20sale%20price%20came%20in%20at%20%243%20billion%2C%20over%2020%20times%20Auditboard's%20valuation%20when%20it%20raised%20its%20Series%20B.%20The%20transaction%20also%20included%20a%20payout%20to%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20startup%20employees%2C%20hearing%20%26quot%3Bbuyout%26quot%3B%20may%20cause%20panic%20with%20visions%20of%20cost%20cutting%20and%20head%20count%20reductions.%20Private%20equity's%20push%20for%20efficiency%20and%20eventual%20profit%20has%20been%20known%20to%20get%20ugly.%20However%2C%20Arnold%20believes%20he's%20found%20a%20champion%20in%20Hg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20Hg%20doesn't%20care%20what%20our%20results%20are%20on%20a%20quarterly%20basis.%20They%20care%20very%20much%2C%20but%20they%20care%20very%20much%20in%20the%20context%20of%20a%20much%20longer-term%20value%20creation%20view%20and%20strategic%20perspective%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnold%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20that.%20That%20was%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we%20really%20cared%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%2019-slide%20pitch%20deck%20that%20AuditBoard%20used%20to%20court%20a%20%243%20billion%20buyout%20from%20private%20equity.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blue%20slide%20from%20a%20presentation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d71db01d8d2deb96b81c84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221687%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAuditBoard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blue%20slide%20from%20a%20presentation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d71db0289b805d1db387c9%3Fformat